value.title: Trump makes 2nd request to Supreme Court over Wisconsin loss
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Wednesday asked the U.S. Supreme Court to overturn his election loss in Wisconsin, his second appeal in as many days to the high court over the result in the key battleground state.

value.title: Biden campaign promises included decriminalizing HIV exposure
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has promised to "advance LGBTQ equality" by reversing decades-old criminalization of HIV exposure and transmission laws that have no "scientific basis" and contribute to stigmas.

value.title: Census Bureau to miss deadline, threatening Trump's attempt to exclude illegal migrants from census
value.excerpt: For the first time in four decades the Census Bureau will miss their deadline on reporting apportionment figures used to divvy up congressional seats.

value.title: Acosta's admission he'll go easier on Biden shows 'personal vendetta' against Trump: Kurtz
value.excerpt: Fox News media analyst Howard Kurtz told "America’s Newsroom" Wednesday that CNN White House correspondent Jim Acosta’s admission he will approach a Biden White House in less adversarial fashion shows he's brought a "personal vendetta" to his reporting on the Trump administration.

value.title: Thomas L. Friedman column: Will Trump force principled conservatives to start their own party? I hope so.
value.excerpt: As the Trump presidency heads into the sunset, kicking and screaming, one of the most important questions that will shape American politics at the local, state and national levels is this: Can Donald Trump maintain his iron grip over the Republican Party when he is out of office?

value.title: President-elect Joe Biden and wife Jill to appear "Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve"
value.excerpt: Hosts and performers for the annual Times Square celebration, which will look different this year due to the pandemic, have also been announced.

value.title: Joe and Jill Biden to appear on Ryan Seacrest's 'New Year's Rockin' Eve'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden and his wife, Dr. Jill Biden, will join Ryan Seacrest on Thursday night's "Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve."

value.title: Trump pardon of Blackwater Iraq contractors violates international law - UN
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump's pardon of four American men convicted of killing Iraqi civilians while working as contractors in 2007 violated U.S. obligations under international law, U.N. human rights experts said on Wednesday.

value.title: Trump campaign asks Supreme Court to review Wisconsin voter fraud case
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign asked for a review before Congress meets to certify the Electoral College's vote on Jan. 6.

value.title: Here's how Mitch McConnell is planning to kill Trump's $2,000 checks
value.excerpt: Less than 48 hours after President Donald Trump claimed that "the Senate will start the process for a vote that increases checks to $2,000, repeals Section 230, and starts an investigation into voter fraud," the actual boss of the Senate had his say.

value.title: Loeffler, Perdue side with Trump on $2,000 stimulus payments
value.excerpt: The Georgia senators, in close runoff races, wouldn’t say whether they’d vote to override the president’s veto of the defense bill.

value.title: Nikki Haley says Americans should be worried about ‘woke left’ when Biden is president
value.excerpt: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley on Tuesday issued a tweet that said Americans should be worried about the "woke left" under President-elect Joe Biden -- warning that the group wants to use the "full force" of government to achieve its radical goals.

value.title: Donald Trump and Michelle Obama named ‘most admired’ in Gallup poll as Dems split 2020 field
value.excerpt: He lost the popular vote and the US election, but Donald Trump was named “most admired” man of 2020 in a new Gallup poll that left Democrats divvying up mentions.

value.title: Trump lashes out at ‘weak and tired’ Republican leaders after House votes to override his veto: ‘A disgraceful act of cowardice’
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump is lashing out at congressional Republicans after the House easily voted to override his veto.

value.title: How Richard Jewell’s Lawyer Became a Pro-Trump Conspiracy Theorist
value.excerpt: The defamation lawyer L. Lin Wood has transformed into a fierce advocate for President Trump whose error-riddled lawsuits have promoted falsehoods about election fraud.

value.title: Trump joins Michelle Obama at top of Gallup's 'Most Admired' lists
value.excerpt: President Trump dethroned former President Barack Obama as the most admired man in 2020, while Obama's wife, Michelle Obama, was named most admired woman for the third year in a row.

value.title: Nashville mayor says Trump still hasn't reached out to him about bombing
value.excerpt: Trump has made no public remarks on the bombing while spending the holidays at his Mar-a-Lago resort in Florida, where he's done a lot of golfing.

value.title: Harris emphasizes COVID-19 vaccine is 'painless' and 'safe'
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris on Tuesday publicly took the recently approved coronavirus vaccine.

value.title: Trump slams 'weak and tired' Senate GOP leaders amid defense veto override fight
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday condemned "weak and tired" Senate Republican leadership as the upper chamber faces a vote to override his veto of the 2021 defense budget.

value.title: Kamala Harris receives first dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine on camera
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris is expected to receive the first dose of a Covid-19 vaccine on Tuesday, according to the Biden transition team.

value.title: Kamala Harris and husband Doug Emhoff receive COVID-19 vaccine
value.excerpt: The vice president-elect received her shot on camera as part of efforts to build public trust in the coronavirus vaccine.

value.title: Biden expected to call out Trump administration on pace of vaccine distribution
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is set to confront the slower-than-expected pace at which the Trump administration is administering coronavirus vaccines in remarks Tuesday afternoon, a transition official tells CNN.

value.title: Trump, Michelle Obama top Gallup's 2020 most admired lists
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump and former first lady Michelle Obama are the most admired man and woman of 2020, according to a new Gallup poll released Tuesday.
